%N A395610 Decimal expansion of 2*asinh(2) + 2*asinh(1/2) + (1 - sqrt(5))/2.
%C A395610 The dimensionless coefficient in the expression for the electrostatic interaction potential between uniformly charged square nanoplate and a uniformly charged nanowire whose length is equal to the side length of the square. They are coplanar, their centers coincide, and the nanowire is parallel to two of the sides of the square.
%C A395610 If Q is the total charge of the nanoplate, q is the total charge of the nanowire, and L is the length of the nanowire and the side of the plate, then the interaction potential is equal to c * k*Q*q/L, where k is the Coulomb constant (A182999) and c is this constant.
%H A395610 Orion Ciftja, <a href="https://doi.org/10.3390/nano13232988">Interaction Potential between a Uniformly Charged Square Nanoplate and Coplanar Nanowire</a>, Nanomaterials, Vol. 13 (2023), Article 2988.
%H A395610 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A395610 Equals 8*log(phi) - 1/phi, where phi is the golden ratio (A001622).
%e A395610 3.23166061172693273177748447302930926736116549527952...
%t A395610 RealDigits[2*ArcSinh[2] + 2*ArcSinh[1/2] + (1 - Sqrt[5])/2, 10, 120][[1]]
%o A395610 (PARI) 2*asinh(2) + 2*asinh(1/2) + (1 - sqrt(5))/2
